---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ScrollReveal from "../components/ScrollReveal.tsx";
import { SITE } from "../config/site.mjs";
---

<Layout
	title={`Colophon | ${SITE.title}`}
	description="The tools, software and services I use to build and run this site"
	canonicalURL={`${SITE.url}/colophon/`}
>
	<Header />
	<main id="main-content" role="main">
		<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-20">
			<ScrollReveal client:idle>
				<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Colophon</h1>
			</ScrollReveal>
			<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.1}>
				<p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-12">
					The tools, software and services I use to build and run this site
				</p>
			</ScrollReveal>

			<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
			<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
				<h2>Overview</h2>
			A colophon is a page or section of a site that describes how the site is made, with what tools, along with its supporting technologies. As long as I've built sits I've enjoyed learning
					what makes other sites tick in order to understand the tools and methods used.
					One site,
					<a
						href="https://builtwith.com/"
						class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
						>BuiltWith</a
					> attempts to break that down on the fly to show you those breadcrumbs,
					and I've made it a habit to list what I use on my sites, so here are the
					tools, software and services I use to build and run Silverbeet.
				</p>
			</ScrollReveal>

			<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
				<h3>Colophon</h3>
				<ul>
					<h4>Tools & Software</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://www.alpinelinux.org/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Alpine Linux</a
							>: an independent, non-commercial, general purpose Linux distribution designed for power users who appreciate security, simplicity and resource efficiency
						</li>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://astro.build/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Astro</a>: 
							a JavaScript web framework optimized for building fast, content-driven websites
						</li>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://docker.com/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Docker</a
							>: an open platform for developing, shipping, and running applications, which enables you to separate your applications from your infrastructure. As a bonus, here's my Docker 
							<a
								href="https://github.com/silverbeet-technology/website/blob/main/compose.yml"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>compose.yml</a
							> file for this site, and its associated
							<a
								href="https://github.com/silverbeet-technology/website/blob/main/.env"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>.env</a
							> environment file it reads during startup
						</li>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://traefik.io/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Traefik</a
							>: a leading modern open source reverse proxy and ingress controller that makes deploying services and APIs easy. As a proxy and load balancer for HTTP and TCP-based applications it can automatically retrieve TLS
							certificates from services like Let's Encrypt
						</li>
						<li>
							<a
								href="https://zed.dev/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>Zed</a
							>: an open source high-performance, multiplayer code editor from the creators of Atom and Tree-sitter, that I really enjoy using
						</li>
					</ul>

					<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
						<h4>Services</h4>
						<ul>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://fastmail.com/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>Fastmail</a
								>: fast, private email hosting for you or your business. More productive, lightning fast, simple and built to save you time
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://github.com/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>GitHub</a
								>: a hosted git platform where you can share code, contribute to open source projects, or even automate your workflow with tools like GitHub Actions and Packages
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://letsencrypt.org/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>Let's Encrypt</a
								>: a free, automated, and open Certificate Authority brought to you by the nonprofit Internet Security Research Group (ISRG) that provides free TLS certificates to more than 700M
								websites
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://porkbun.com/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>Porkbun</a
								>: an ICANN accredited domain name registrar based out of the Pacific Northwest providing DNS service
							</li>
							<li>
								<a
									href="https://vultr.com/"
									class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
									>Vultr</a
								>: a cloud server service offering fast SSD VPS cloud servers with 100% KVM virtualization for global cloud hosting
							</li>
						</ul>
					</ScrollReveal>

					<ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
						<h3>Interesting?</h3>
						<p>
							I hope that was interesting, for those following along, here's the
							<a
								href="https://builtwith.com/silverbeet.tech/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>BuiltWith Silverbeet page</a
							> which lists a few extraneous bits it found running the site. If you'd like to discuss your site, application or infrastructure and how it could be setup, feel free to
							<a
								href="/contact/"
								class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 transition-colors"
								>contact</a
							> me to start a dialog.
						</p>
					</ScrollReveal>
				</ul>
			</ScrollReveal>
		</section>
		<Footer />
	</main>
</Layout>
